	abstract = {An improved Kjeldahl digestion technique permits precise determination of dissolved organic nitrogen in freshwater samples. Prior to digestion, ammonia inherent in sample water was removed by an evaporator at low temperature under alkaline conditions. The ammonia produced by Kjeldahl digestion was determined colorimetrically. The proposed method was relatively simple but proved to be sufficient for routine analysis of DON in fresh waters, having distinct advantages over other wet oxidation methods for DON analysis. DON concentration was measured with high accuracy and showed little scatter, even for water samples from eutrophic areas and deep layers containing a large amount of dissolved inorganic nitrogen.},
